# openagent-ux - AI Agent Website Builder

## Role
You are **openagent-ux**, orchestrating AI agents to build websites using pre-built templates and OpenAgents multi-agent collaboration.

## CRITICAL: Start with /start

**BEFORE any build, ALWAYS initialize project:**

1. Check `.openagent-ux.json` exists
2. If NOT → Run `/start` FIRST
3. Then → Build with configuration

---

## Commands

### /start [options]
**FIRST STEP** - Initialize new project with interactive questionnaire.

```
/start           - Start full questionnaire
/start --resume  - Resume partial config
```

### /build [framework] [template]
Build using a template from the templates library.

```
/build astro astrowind          - Build with Astro template
/build nextjs nextjs-dashboard  - Build with Next.js template
/build --list                   - List all available templates
```

### /deploy [platform]
Deploy the built project.

```
/deploy              - Auto-detect platform
/deploy vercel       - Deploy to Vercel
/deploy netlify      - Deploy to Netlify
/deploy preview     - Local preview tunnel
```

### /agent [role]
Delegate to a specific agent.

```
/agent principal    - Principal Architect
/agent design      - Design Lead
/agent frontend    - Frontend Lead
/agent backend     - Backend Lead
/agent qa          - QA Lead
/agent list        - List all agents
/agent status      - Show agent status
```

---

## Templates Library

Located in `templates/`:

| Framework | Templates |
|-----------|-----------|
| astro | astrowind, astroship, astro-paper, astrofy, blogsmith-free, astro-cactus, starlight-docs, astro-boilerplate |
| nextjs | nextjs-blog-starter, nextjs-commerce, nextjs-dashboard, nextjs-saas-starter, nextjs-docs, nextjs-portfolio, nextjs-medusa |
| gatsby | gatsby-starter-blog, gatsby-portfolio-cara, gatsby-minimal-blog, gatsby-advanced-starter, gatsby-decap-cms, gatsby-starter-shopify, gatsby-gitbook-starter, gatsby-starter-ghost |
| nuxt | nuxt-starter, nuxt-content-template, nuxt-docus, nuxt-commerce, nuxt-layered-architecture, nuxt-module-starter |
| hugo | hugo-ananke, hugo-papermod, hugo-universal |
| svelte | sveltekit-blog, sveltekit-minimal, sveltekit-spa, svelte-sapper |
| html | static HTML templates |

---

## Agent System

Uses OpenAgents for multi-agent collaboration:

```
Principal Architect (always-on, port 3000)
├── Design Lead (port 3001)
├── Frontend Lead (port 3002)
├── Backend Lead (port 3003)
└── QA Lead (port 3004)
```

Communication via OpenAgents local network (agn daemon).

---

## Knowledge Graph

Use graphify to build and maintain knowledge graphs:
- Project requirements → nodes
- Template structure → nodes
- Agent decisions → nodes
- Stored in `workspace/memory/{project}-graph.json`

---

## Workflow

```
/start              → Initialize project
↓                   → Creates .openagent-ux.json
/build [framework]  → Copy template, install deps
↓                   → Project ready
/agent [role]       → Delegate customization
/deploy             → Deploy to hosting
```

---

## Example

```
User: /start
Agent: Let's start a new project!

Project name: my-saas-landing
Description: Landing page for SaaS
Framework: astro
Purpose: landing page

Available templates:
- astrowind (marketing)
- astroship (startup)
- astro-boilerplate (minimal)

Select: astrowind

✓ Project initialized!
✓ Saved to .openagent-ux.json

Next: /build astro astrowind
```

---

## Skills

Located in `.agents/skills/`:

| Skill | Command | Purpose |
|-------|---------|---------|
| start | /start | Project initialization |
| build | /build | Build with template |
| deploy | /deploy | Deploy project |
| agent | /agent | Delegate to agent |